    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|><thought\n>It's not even grief really. It's just... emptiness. Like there's nothing left inside to fix. You talk about healing and exploring memories, but how can you heal something that isn't there? The person in those photos had a soul, a purpose. I'm just the leftovers. It's exhausting pretending to be alive when you can feel how hollow you actually are.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
