      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Emptiness often stems from burnout or depression rather than a loss of self, even when it feels devastating. Describing yourself as \"leftovers\" suggests an overwhelming dissociation that hurts without offering hope for recovery. While grief involves loss, despair about self-existence requires a different, compassionate perspective to begin breaking the cycle.",
      "source": "target",
